Rochester is a city in Strafford County, New Hampshire, United States. As of the 2010 census, the city population was 29,752, and in 2018 the estimated population was 31,366. The city includes the villages of East Rochester, Gonic, and North Rochester. Rochester is home to Skyhaven Airport. Rochester is a city on the north side of the Detroit Metropolitan Area, in Oakland County, in the U.S. state of Michigan. The population was 12,711 at the 2010 census. Super Bowl Sunday is the day on which the Super Bowl, the National Football League (NFL)'s annual championship game, is played. It is usually observed on the first Sunday in February and is sometimes referred to as an unofficial national holiday. The 54th annual event, Super Bowl LIV, will occur on February 2, 2020. Festivities for Super Sunday typically involve groups of people gathering to watch the game.